race.comment: WALK WITH PRIDE (7) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fifth (26.62) in a Grade 5 NP at this track. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. GAME OF PHONES (3) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish third, beaten 6 lengths (26.26) at Warragul in a Grade 5 NP over 460m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Racing well and deserves a win. AXEL'S RADAR (1) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (22.82) at this track behind Special Teams in a Grade 5. Worked home well on that occasion and should be strong late. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and four minor placings to his credit. Will give a great sight again. MYALL MEG (2) is worth a look despite no experience at this circuit.
